##Implementation of the project

To run this project in the folder /Cangrow-project/section3, follow the steps below:

1. Clone the project from your personal GitHub repository or the main project repository using the following command in your terminal:

```shell
     git clone https://github.com/roxi-t/Cangrow-Project.git```
in directory 
 a directory named Cangrow-Project has been created

2. Go to the project directory and create an .env file. Set the required environment variables in the .env file using the KEY=VALUE format.

3. Optionally, you can modify the docker-compose.yml file to customize the settings.

4. Use Docker Compose to start the service in detached mode:

cd /Cangrow-Project/section3
docker-compose up -d

In this directory are all the necessary files to run this project

5. You should now be able to access your WordPress website at http://localhost or your server IP address. You will also have access to the database where you have previously stored the desired data.

Now you can access your WordPress website and its associated database and take advantage of the load balancing and database management capabilities provided by ProxySQL.
